# .clinerules — Roo/Cline Specific Notes

Core agent rules, conventions, and SDLC process are defined in `AGENTS.md`.

---

## Roo/Cline Specifics

- Use `new_task` (boomerang mode) to spawn subagents.
- Set the mode appropriately: `code`, `ask`, or `architect`.
- Roo has good support for parallel tasks.
- Always read `sdlc-gitmcp` and Context7 when needed.

See `AGENTS.md` for:
- Session opening and closing protocol
- All commands
- Subagent system and triggers
- Core conventions